5
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:15,300
{\pos(120,234)}YYeTs.com

14
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,770
Previously on "Salem"...

15
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,790
- Do you ever wonder? - What?

16
00:00:04,790 --> 00:00:06,430
If we could leave this place?

17
00:00:09,710 --> 00:00:11,520
Gloriana, you mustn't be here.

18
00:00:11,550 --> 00:00:13,520
What will you do here --

19
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:15,090
in the house of the lord?

20
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:23,010
What the hell are you doing here, Hooke?

21
00:00:23,010 --> 00:00:25,100
Now, careful, captain... unless you do not mind me

22
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,290
telling the good people of salem

23
00:00:26,290 --> 00:00:28,940
just who john alden really is.

24
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:30,850
The package shall be yours by midnight.

25
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:45,230
The familiar has been cut from her.

26
00:00:45,230 --> 00:00:46,180
How?

27
00:00:46,550 --> 00:00:47,660
An exorcism...

28
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,420
performed by her dolt of a father, no doubt.

29
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:52,620
So we must replace it.

30
00:00:52,650 --> 00:00:53,640
My god.

31
00:00:53,870 --> 00:00:56,440
The girl has been rendered frail by her circumstance.

32
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:58,330
She needs but a moment of rest.

33
00:00:58,330 --> 00:00:59,960
After which, she will again be strong enough

34
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:01,130
to point the finger.

35
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:02,680
Open your mouth.

36
00:01:05,950 --> 00:01:08,270
I know what you are.

37
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:18,250
Get 'em into a room, will ya?

38
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:20,200
I'll be back in two shakes.

39
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,100
You're leaving?

40
00:01:21,870 --> 00:01:22,950
Are you deaf, girl?

41
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,130
Get 'em into a room!

42
00:01:25,570 --> 00:01:26,450
Yes, mum.

44
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:39,930
I do not.

45
00:02:40,090 --> 00:02:43,500
Yo'a'nes John Alden.

46
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:46,350
John Alden.

47
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:47,870
Yes?

50
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,510
Yes. Yes.

54
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:18,420
Yet, you say the man who holds the secret is dead.

57
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,560
Are we certain we can trust her?

59
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:39,900
I'm not so sure the servant is loyal.

60
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:43,640
I used to think your stubbornness a virtue.

61
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,090
And you don't any longer?

62
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:48,960
Why go alone when there is influence in numbers?

63
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,670
The girl has shown her color.

64
00:03:50,690 --> 00:03:52,850
We are well beyond the point of intimidation.

65
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:55,440
Then perhaps we are at the point of elimination.

66
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,760
Perhaps, but for the time being,

67
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:01,500
She is worth much more to us alive than dead.

68
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:16,080
*Pound me the witch drums*

69
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:17,120
*Witch drums*

70
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:20,660
*Pound me the witch drums*

71
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:23,890
*Pound me the witch drums*

72
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,130
*The witch drums*

73
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:27,670
*Better pray for hell*

74
00:04:27,670 --> 00:04:33,750
*Not hallelujah*

75
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:00,170
Look who's here, Mercy. Mrs.Sibley.

76
00:05:01,010 --> 00:05:02,600
-Sit up straight, girl. - Leave us.

77
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:04,990
Leave us, reverend.

78
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,010
Yes.

79
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,040
Certainly.

80
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:17,330
You came to visit me last night.

81
00:05:17,910 --> 00:05:18,860
Did I?

82
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:21,510
The time for coyness has passed.

83
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:26,920
It is clear you know exactly who and what I am.

84
00:05:27,990 --> 00:05:30,060
The only question that remains

85
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:32,410
is what you will do with that information.

86
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,200
That depends on you, Mrs. Sibley.

87
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,710
What do you want, girl?

88
00:05:43,220 --> 00:05:45,180
I want it to stop...

89
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:50,490
the torture, the torment, the suffering.

90
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:54,050
Or I will tell them.

91
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:57,580
I will tell them all who and what you are.

92
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,000
You know nothing of me...

93
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:05,070
or what I've done or given up

94
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,650
or endured to be who I am.

95
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:12,580
You are tortured because you resist.

96
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:18,150
Give in to me, and you will know only pleasure.

97
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:19,910
You torture me.

98
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:24,410
You put the snake inside of me.

99
00:06:24,410 --> 00:06:26,670
You are the hag that bites my shoulder.

100
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:29,410
Careful, or your foolishness

101
00:06:29,410 --> 00:06:32,390
will come to overshadow your usefulness.

102
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:35,600
You live still...

103
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:38,530
because I allow it.

104
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,500
You breathe only because I wish it.

105
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,790
You would kill me?

106
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,700
If you speak.

107
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,560
Stay silent, and you shall live.

108
00:06:58,820 --> 00:07:02,010
My heart is deep and full.

109
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:06,820
It yearns to give you further chance to prove your worth.

110
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:10,870
Fail me, and you fail yourself.

111
00:07:14,450 --> 00:07:16,360
The crag awaits your decision.

112
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:46,590
Damn it.

113
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:13,670
You sent for me?

114
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:15,380
Yes.

115
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,310
If your purpose is further humiliation

116
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:20,710
or probings of the heart,

117
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:22,870
I, for one, have had my fill.

118
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,740
My purpose is a proposition.

119
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,470
A business arrangement of sorts.

120
00:09:31,850 --> 00:09:32,830
I'm listening.

121
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:36,060
In which you would tell me

122
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:38,280
the sum of your most fruitful week's bounty,

123
00:09:39,770 --> 00:09:43,170
and I shall provide double in perpetuity...

124
00:09:44,930 --> 00:09:46,030
for your company...

125
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:49,680
and your precious time...

126
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:53,650
in exclusivity.

127
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:02,870
So you wish to buy me outright.

128
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:06,400
I'm an only child.

129
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:10,320
I never learned to share.

130
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:14,150
Which is as close as a man like you comes to an apology.

131
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,050
Was it really so very painful for you

132
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:20,280
to see me with another?

133
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:23,590
Yes.

134
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,230
Will you be mine?

135
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:05,690
Cotton.

136
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,780
Captain Alden!

137
00:11:12,090 --> 00:11:13,250
What brings you here?

138
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:21,900
This.

139
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:28,930
Are you sure, Dottie?

140
00:11:28,930 --> 00:11:30,820
Are you sure she won't hurt us?

141
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:32,460
'Course she won't hurt us...

142
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,830
...unless you be a witch.

143
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:42,940
Hello, Mercy.

144
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,650
May we come in?

145
00:12:05,570 --> 00:12:07,270
They come to you in your room, Mercy?

146
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:08,980
Them...

147
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:10,980
witches?

148
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,340
Sometimes...

149
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,040
And other times in other places.

150
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,860
Are they here with us now?

151
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,140
Can you see them as we speak?

152
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,990
No, I don't see them now.

153
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,580
Do they hurt you?

154
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:35,950
Sometimes.

155
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:37,910
What's it like?

156
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,880
What's it like?

157
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,960
To point your finger

158
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:45,660
and make them shake and tremble with fear.

159
00:12:45,660 --> 00:12:48,000
To point your finger and watch them run.

160
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:52,160
No, it's not like that...

161
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,950
at all.

162
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:55,410
I swear.

163
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:58,820
No woman in Salem has ever had that kind of power.

164
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:00,750
Not even Mary Sibley.

165
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:18,640
You think I have sway...

166
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:22,780
...amongst all the people of Salem?

167
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:27,020
Your little finger points to life a-and death itself.

168
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:30,880
Tell us... what do the witches look like?

169
00:13:37,780 --> 00:13:38,990
One more thing, Mrs. Sibley...

170
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,310
There was an overflow of parcels left on the britania,

171
00:13:41,310 --> 00:13:44,050
all of which are to be delivered to a William Hooke.

172
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,320
Now, we've looked high and low.

173
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,860
No one could seem to locate the fellow.

174
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:49,450
I see. I'll take care of it.

175
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:50,470
Thank you, madam.

176
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:55,040
They will not find Mr. Hooke... not now, not ever.

177
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,610
I won't ask what happened to him.

178
00:13:56,610 --> 00:13:57,600
Nor should you.

179
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:00,680
Then contain it before curiosity grows.

180
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:04,390
Uh, Mrs. Sibley, uh, good afternoon.

181
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:06,610
Might I borrow your girl?

182
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:10,760
The missus has taken ill with a batch of wayward mussels

183
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:14,790
and now begs relief with one of her exceptional tonics.

184
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:19,090
Please send Mrs. Hale my most urgent regrets.

185
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:20,720
Most kind.

186
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,910
Oh, Mr. Richards, uh, fetch for me a list of items

187
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,770
this Mr. Hooke was here to receive,

188
00:14:32,770 --> 00:14:35,100
one that also perhaps includes their site of origin.

189
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:36,020
Right away, madam.

190
00:14:37,070 --> 00:14:38,610
Your lie is clumsy.

191
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:40,020
No one is ill.

192
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:42,370
My mistress can see that as clearly as I.

193
00:14:42,370 --> 00:14:45,050
Yes, well, when it comes to lies and subterfuge,

194
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,660
I defer to your expert endowments.

195
00:14:47,690 --> 00:14:50,410
State your purpose or be gone with you.

196
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:53,700
My purpose is to rid this town of John Alden

197
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,170
once and for all,

198
00:14:57,410 --> 00:15:00,190
unless that is a purpose for which you lack interest.

199
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:12,360
That was the same girl...

200
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:14,730
from Lamb's,

201
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,200
the one you threw a punch over.

202
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,130
Was it?

203
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,710
Wasn't aware they made outcalls.

204
00:15:25,420 --> 00:15:27,150
Tell me again of the visions.

205
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,720
Yellowed faces...

206
00:15:34,110 --> 00:15:37,980
bodies overcome by rash and blister...

207
00:15:39,150 --> 00:15:41,090
death in great numbers.

208
00:15:41,570 --> 00:15:43,860
And this came to you as the artifact was brought to life?

209
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:45,650
Yep.

210
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:48,910
Where did you say it came from?

211
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,930
Where everything in this town comes from... a ship.

212
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:03,760
Ritum Magni.

213
00:16:08,830 --> 00:16:09,900
The grand rite?

214
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:13,840
Most of what we know is lore... rumor, legend.

215
00:16:14,470 --> 00:16:16,830
It says this object, this "Malum,"

216
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:17,820
has thought to be present

217
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:19,690
at every grand rite throughout history.

218
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,470
Everything I have read has said that the grand rite

219
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:24,950
has only ever been attempted, never completed.

220
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,760
Maybe plague's only part of it.

221
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:28,670
This object is evil.

222
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:32,170
It consecrates the earth for the devil's return.

223
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,660
It was here for delivery. Someone was expecting it.

224
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:37,990
A witch.

225
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:42,130
We must inform the selectmen immediately.

226
00:16:42,970 --> 00:16:43,870
No.

227
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,680
No?

228
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,290
We have something the witches want.

229
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:50,590
What better way to get their attention?

230
00:16:50,950 --> 00:16:52,710
What better way to get yourself killed?

231
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:54,540
We are all in danger,

232
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,070
but I would rather die

233
00:16:56,070 --> 00:16:59,140
before Salem's finest control my fate.

234
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:04,280
Are you with me?

235
00:17:12,590 --> 00:17:14,710
Not over there, you infernal mutant!

236
00:17:14,890 --> 00:17:15,900
Over here!

237
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,320
That's him.

238
00:18:19,620 --> 00:18:22,510
And the magistrate's true purpose in taking you from me?

239
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:25,400
My eyes betrayed my sense

240
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,680
when I came upon Mrs. Hale bent over her chamber pot.

241
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:34,130
If you insist upon this lie,

242
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:35,620
it forces me to ask

243
00:18:35,670 --> 00:18:38,990
where you're off to now with such great urgency.

244
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,760
The apotek.

245
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:44,220
I run low on the bark of cascara sagrada.

246
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,340
By all means.

247
00:19:06,970 --> 00:19:09,210
It's like the great flowing robe of the pope.

248
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:11,320
Or the jeweled-up crown of a king.

249
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,920
Well, it's quite disagreeable on -- I assure you.

250
00:19:15,570 --> 00:19:16,720
Just think of it...

251
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:18,700
being led through the market

252
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,700
by the handsome reverend Mather.

253
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:24,310
What's he like, Mercy, hmm?

254
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,730
Does he speak of God and demons?

255
00:19:27,690 --> 00:19:29,580
We've spoke many times.

256
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:32,550
He's shown great interest in my affliction.

257
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:34,860
It's you who points the finger...

258
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:39,090
while all of Salem holds their breath and waits.

259
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:42,590
Well, it's not exactly like that. I...

260
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:46,150
If I had your say-so, I know who I'd accuse.

261
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:48,110
Who?

262
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,220
Who?

263
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,220
It's her father.

264
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:01,140
She'd accuse her own father.

265
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:05,310
Why?

266
00:20:11,770 --> 00:20:14,230
Makes her sing in the streets all day long

267
00:20:14,230 --> 00:20:16,430
while he nurses the bottle at Lamb's --

268
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,980
Sing and beg.

269
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:23,320
Then he takes what coin she's made for spirits

270
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:26,400
and beats her senseless for her troubles.

271
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,970
Is this true?

272
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:35,570
I'm to be 15 next month,

273
00:20:35,690 --> 00:20:39,010
and he swears to sell me to the Rod.

274
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:44,750
Your father means to sell you to the whorehouse?

275
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,660
I'll run away.

276
00:20:47,910 --> 00:20:51,460
Even if he sells me, I'm -- I'll run.

277
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,490
No one is running away.

278
00:20:58,360 --> 00:20:59,280
No one.

280
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:04,710
Sinner or savior!

281
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,430
How are we to know?!

282
00:21:07,050 --> 00:21:09,630
Look but to the torment of the damned,

283
00:21:09,630 --> 00:21:13,680
and think well of the difference betwixt angels and devils,

284
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:18,510
and you will know what sin is and where sin resides!

285
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,970
How 'bout you not rile the crowd further than they are?

286
00:21:23,310 --> 00:21:24,580
It's two bits a sheet.

287
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:27,960
I'm still full up here, unless you'd like to buy me out.

288
00:21:29,170 --> 00:21:31,160
Be loads more fun to beat you stupid.

289
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,620
Miss Hale.

290
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:35,840
Captain Alden.

291
00:21:37,910 --> 00:21:39,040
It's a fine day.

292
00:21:39,670 --> 00:21:40,520
Is it?

293
00:21:41,390 --> 00:21:42,370
Perhaps not.

294
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,460
Oh, indeed. Perhaps not.

295
00:21:44,930 --> 00:21:47,770
Perhaps there will be no more fine days in Salem.

296
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:51,160
Perhaps the days of fine days are tragically behind us.

297
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:53,610
Have I offended you, Miss Hale?

298
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:01,060
Do you consider it offensive

299
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:03,400
raising hope in a heart most normally well-guarded

300
00:22:03,410 --> 00:22:05,150
while your own beats in the breast of another?

301
00:22:05,430 --> 00:22:07,300
Do you, Captain Alden, find that reprehensible

302
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:09,440
- or simply unkind? - Well, I...

303
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,070
Or, most likely, you think not of it at all

304
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:13,790
or me or others, as is the wont and practice of most men.

305
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:16,230
Ah, Mrs. Sibley.

306
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:18,740
Anne.

307
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,180
Perfect.

308
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,390
Are you ever grateful to be no longer young?

309
00:22:30,340 --> 00:22:31,110
Yes.

310
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:35,430
