311
00:22:37,780 --> 00:22:39,070
I was never that young.

312
00:22:41,630 --> 00:22:44,200
We were both...once.

313
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,180
What brings you to market?

314
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:52,980
Tituba.

315
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:55,510
We were to meet at the herbalist.

316
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,550
A fine pair you two make in this place of death.

317
00:23:15,550 --> 00:23:16,420
Give it to her.

318
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:22,450
It will take time.

319
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:25,580
And you will report to me as soon as you're finished.

320
00:23:25,580 --> 00:23:26,770
Afraid to stay?

321
00:23:28,390 --> 00:23:30,580
My time is better spent elsewhere.

322
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:32,640
For the best.

323
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:35,990
Once a man dabbles in the dark arts,

324
00:23:35,990 --> 00:23:38,580
it's difficult for him to return to the light.

325
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,280
Fetch me a rabbit.

326
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,770
Y-yes.

327
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,520
Get on there!

328
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,300
Mrs. Sibley.

329
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:54,840
Mrs. Browning.

330
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:57,230
Oh. No need to turn away.

331
00:23:57,230 --> 00:23:59,540
He is an arresting figure.

332
00:23:59,540 --> 00:24:04,130
Only my old lady's eyes that keep me from staring myself.

333
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:05,600
Don't be ridiculous.

334
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:09,410
You still insist on ignoring my expertise.

335
00:24:09,410 --> 00:24:10,120
Yep.

336
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:12,470
There are less pedestrian,

337
00:24:12,470 --> 00:24:14,090
less painful methods,

338
00:24:14,090 --> 00:24:16,010
with which we could accomplish our goals.

339
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:19,580
It must happen tonight.

340
00:24:19,930 --> 00:24:21,570
There will be no second chances.

341
00:24:21,570 --> 00:24:23,810
The ways of the common are always good enough for me.

342
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:31,690
And if it causes pain, so much the better.

343
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:36,640
Still in a brown study, I see.

344
00:24:37,090 --> 00:24:39,290
Hasn't spoken a word all day.

345
00:24:39,930 --> 00:24:41,230
Mm. Well, she'll recover.

346
00:24:41,740 --> 00:24:42,580
From what?

347
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:44,900
- What did you say to her? - Nothing.

348
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,930
Merely trying to spare her heart the inevitable woe.

349
00:24:49,430 --> 00:24:51,050
Worry not, my husband.

350
00:24:51,650 --> 00:24:53,050
This will all be distant memory

351
00:24:53,050 --> 00:24:55,240
Once she's become Mrs. Cotton Mather.

352
00:25:00,060 --> 00:25:01,080
I wonder.

353
00:25:02,010 --> 00:25:02,940
Wonder what?

354
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:08,500
If he'd never left, if you'd been allowed to marry,

355
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:11,790
and found yourself now in that house of his

356
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:14,490
with three squalling brats,

357
00:25:14,490 --> 00:25:17,740
working ceaselessly to spread your meager wages...

358
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:22,570
Would Captain Alden still hold such desperate appeal?

359
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:29,610
Or is it that you're trapped in first bliss,

360
