446
00:32:39,310 --> 00:32:42,330
John Alden will not leave town for a gambling debt.

447
00:32:44,250 --> 00:32:45,940
That's what she told you?

448
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,480
She lied?

449
00:32:48,590 --> 00:32:49,740
I'll beat it out of her.

450
00:32:49,740 --> 00:32:50,970
No.

451
00:32:51,220 --> 00:32:54,830
Does Tituba not yearn for the grand rite?

452
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:57,970
Is there another, in fact, that craves it more?

453
00:33:00,180 --> 00:33:02,660
So she'll use the real secret.

454
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:06,220
In her own way, but for the same purpose --

455
00:33:06,220 --> 00:33:07,880
to control Mary.

456
00:33:11,430 --> 00:33:13,600
We have another problem.

457
00:33:14,870 --> 00:33:17,950
The object William Hooke was tasked to deliver

458
00:33:17,950 --> 00:33:20,140
has fallen into other hands.

459
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:25,110
And what exactly was William Hooke tasked to deliver?

460
00:33:28,180 --> 00:33:29,580
The Malum.

461
00:33:31,750 --> 00:33:32,780
The Malum?

462
00:33:33,180 --> 00:33:36,020
We must be prepared for every eventuality,

463
00:33:36,020 --> 00:33:38,850
even one that does not include Mary Sibley.

464
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:40,800
That is the malum's purpose.

465
00:33:42,340 --> 00:33:43,560
Who has it?

466
00:33:46,180 --> 00:33:47,620
John Alden.

467
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,950
I looked for you at market.

468
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,320
The apotek ran low.

469
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,120
I was forced to pick the bark myself.

470
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:23,700
The next lie to cross your lips will be your last.

471
00:34:25,930 --> 00:34:30,040
You would threaten me, your one true ally?

472
00:34:32,020 --> 00:34:33,890
So the others have turned on me.

473
00:34:33,890 --> 00:34:34,780
Yes.

474
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:38,960
- Who?  - Each and every one.

475
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:41,860
Rose?

476
00:34:42,410 --> 00:34:43,410
Everyone.

477
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,730
They meet in secret,

478
00:34:47,630 --> 00:34:49,530
speak of your weakness,

479
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:54,020
plot to rid Salem of John Alden.

480
00:34:54,020 --> 00:34:56,140
Fearful he has taken me from myself.

481
00:34:56,140 --> 00:34:56,930
Yes.

482
00:34:57,330 --> 00:34:58,440
Nonsense.

483
00:34:59,180 --> 00:35:00,880
I am most completely myself!

484
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:01,850
You are not!

485
00:35:03,030 --> 00:35:05,180
You are in love.

486
00:35:08,100 --> 00:35:11,890
Let me tell you about him -- this man that you love.

487
00:35:12,590 --> 00:35:13,980
He is a murderer.

488
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:16,470
- He is not. - Yes.

489
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:20,080
And he has killed yet another to keep his secret.

490
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:24,090
If I tell the magistrate, the militia will come,

491
00:35:24,090 --> 00:35:26,370
they will take him, and they will hang him.

492
00:35:29,570 --> 00:35:30,660
Lies.

493
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:34,340
If you wish for John Alden to live,

494
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:36,320
you will complete the grand rite.

495
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:39,290
The next moon will see eight more dead.

496
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,400
Lies.

497
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:46,960
The dead don't lie.

498
00:35:53,750 --> 00:35:54,980
Hello, father.

499
00:36:00,970 --> 00:36:02,440
I'm locked up.

500
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,490
Yes, you are.

501
00:36:04,270 --> 00:36:05,320
What for?

502
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:07,740
You're a witch.

503
00:36:10,770 --> 00:36:14,540
A drunk, a card sharp, a two-timer, maybe.

504
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:15,590
But a witch?

505
00:36:21,030 --> 00:36:22,320
I think not.

506
00:36:24,660 --> 00:36:26,360
I come to say goodbye.

507
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:29,870
and thanks for nothing.

508
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:34,170
I'll be out of here in no time,

509
00:36:35,170 --> 00:36:39,060
and then you will be sold, just like we planned.

510
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:42,230
Or you'll hang...

511
00:36:43,330 --> 00:36:44,540
Or burn.

512
00:36:49,570 --> 00:36:51,140
We'll see, father.

513
00:36:53,290 --> 00:36:54,270
We'll see.

514
00:36:57,940 --> 00:36:59,010
Miss Hopkins?

515
00:37:02,090 --> 00:37:03,430
Miss -- miss Hale.

516
00:37:04,420 --> 00:37:06,900
A small collection to help ease your circumstances

517
00:37:06,910 --> 00:37:08,390
in this most trying time.

518
00:37:11,970 --> 00:37:12,970
Thank you.

519
00:37:14,070 --> 00:37:15,490
He'll get a fair trial.

520
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:18,410
My father will see to that,

521
00:37:19,260 --> 00:37:20,870
or I'll see to my father.

522
00:37:23,450 --> 00:37:25,050
You're most kind, Miss Hale.

523
00:37:25,330 --> 00:37:28,920
